Package org.neo4j.internal.index.label

Class NativeTokenScanStore

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.neo4j.internal.index.label.NativeTokenScanStore
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    TokenScanStore, ConsistencyCheckable, Lifecycle, EntityTokenUpdateListener
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    NativeLabelScanStore, NativeRelationshipTypeScanStore
    public abstract class NativeTokenScanStore
extends Object
implements TokenScanStore, EntityTokenUpdateListener
    Implements TokenScanStore and thus also implements LabelScanStore. Uses GBPTree atop a PageCache. Only a single writer is allowed at any given point in time so synchronization or merging of updates need to be handled externally.

    About the Layout used in this instance of GBPTree:

    • Each keys is a combination of entityId and entityIdRange (entityId/64).
    • Each value is a 64-bit bit set (a primitive long) where each set bit in it represents an entity with that token, such that entityId = entityIdRange+bitOffset.

    force(IOLimiter, PageCursorTracer) is vital for allowing this store to be recoverable, and must be called whenever Neo4j performs a checkpoint.

    This store is backed by a single store file, "neostore.labelscanstore.db" for LabelScanStore.

      • newReader

        public TokenScanReader newReader()
        Specified by:
        newReader in interface TokenScanStore
        Returns:
        TokenScanReader capable of finding entity ids with given token ids. Readers will immediately see updates made by TokenScanWriter, although TokenScanWriter may internally batch updates so functionality isn't reliable. The only given is that readers will see at least updates from closed writers.
